film sets. Cooper Lace was the first company to introduce a lace curtain panel designed by William Morris and has become the leading resource for Arts &amp; Crafts and Victorian lace window treatments. Dan is also a well-known author, and has published over a thousand articles on the subjects of antiques, architecture, preservation and historic interior design in such magazines as <a href=\"http://www.oldhouseinteriors.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Old House Interiors</a>, <a href=\"http://artsandcraftshomes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Arts &amp; Crafts Homes</a>, <a href=\"http://www.oldhousejournal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Old House Journal</a>, <a href=\"http://www.period-homes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Period Homes</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.antiquehomesmagazine.com/info.php?info_id=70\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Antique Homes</a>. His first book, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/New-Classic-American-Houses-Architecture/dp/0865652538\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">New Classic American Houses</a>, was published by The Vendome Press. <img src=\"https://www.cottagelace.com/images/stairrail.jpg\" alt=\"Stair Case\" width=\"140\" height=\"134\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" />\n\nDan is also recognized as a leading authority on the subject of historic carpeting. He has traveled throughout North America consulting on and purveying historic Wilton, Brussels, Axminster, Ingrain and Venetian carpets, and has worked in hundreds of state capitols, governor\'s mansions, decorative arts and house museums, including a notable residence in the District of Columbia. Please visit <a href=\"http://www.historic-carpet.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">www.historic-carpet.com</a> for more information.\";s:18:\"responsive_display\";s:0:\"\";s:18:\"visibility_display\";s:0:\"\";s:26:\"visibility_user_capability\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"animation\";